# banking-finance

Spring Boot banking service with full CI/CD pipeline on AWS EKS.

## Repo structure

```
banking-finance/
├── src/                        ← Spring Boot application (existing)
├── k8s/
│   └── deployment.yaml         ← Kubernetes deployment + service
├── docs/
│   └── design-document.md      ← CI/CD and infrastructure design write-up
├── Dockerfile                  ← existing
├── Jenkinsfile                 ← CI/CD pipeline definition
└── README.md
```

## Branch → Environment

| Branch | Environment | Approval needed? |
|--------|-------------|-----------------|
| `feature/*` | qa | No |
| `develop` | qa | No |
| `staging` | staging | No |
| `main` | prod | Yes — manual gate in Jenkins |

## Pipeline stages

1. Set environment (reads branch name)
2. Checkout code from GitHub
3. Run unit tests — stops if any test fails
4. Build JAR with Maven
5. Build Docker image
6. Push image to AWS ECR (ap-south-1)
7. Deploy to EKS namespace
8. Health check — auto-rollback if it fails

## Infrastructure

- **Compute:** AWS EKS (ap-south-1) — `banking-cluster`
- **Registry:** AWS ECR — `banking-finance`
- **CI/CD:** Jenkins on EC2 Ubuntu
- **Deployment type:** Rolling (zero downtime)
- **Credentials:** IAM Role on Jenkins EC2 — no hardcoded keys

## Quick commands

```bash
# Check pods in any environment
kubectl get pods -n qa
kubectl get pods -n staging
kubectl get pods -n prod

# Get the app URL
kubectl get svc banking-finance -n qa

# Manual rollback
kubectl rollout undo deployment/banking-finance -n qa
```

